<DOC><DOCNO> ZF32-230-031 </DOCNO><DOCID>10 374 530</DOCID><JOURNAL>DG Review  Feb 1991 v11 n8 p8(4).andM;</JOURNAL><TITLE>Speeding up ?FSTAT: finding and eliminating a system bottleneck.andO;</TITLE><AUTHOR>Horvitz, Phil.andM;</AUTHOR><TEXT><ABSTRACT>Performance tuning shows that VS/II systems respond very well.andO;Tests show that a heavy demand on a system can be caused by linkresolution and numerous complex pathnames; this can result in poorperformance.andP;  An alternative approach to using full pathnames isto DIR into the target directory and use only the simple filenameto perform the ?FSTAT call.andP;  This should make a VS/II system runfaster.andP;  New benchmark results show that a considerable amount ofCPU can be saved by using simple filnames in place of fullpathnames where directory scans are being performed on complexdirectory structures.andP;  Reducing both the depth and number of linksin frequently accessed directories can also result in betterperformance.andM;</ABSTRACT></TEXT><DESCRIPT>Product:   VS II (Operating system) (Usage).andO;Topic:     Performance MeasurementPerformance ImprovementBenchmarksOperating Systems.andO;Feature:   illustrationtable.andO;Caption:   Benchmark results ?FSTAT performance. (table)andM;</DESCRIPT></DOC>